CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 14, 1955, pg. 14 reads: "First Anniversary-Purity Chapter 85, Order of Eastern Star, celebrated its first anniversary on Friday, April 29, at Masonic Temple. Seated: Isabel Hunter, worthy matron; James Dukes, worthy patron; Mildred Smith, Esther Green, Grand Vorthy Matron of the State of Pennsylvania; Eva Crawley, Grand Associate Matron; Mary Smith, Grand Traveling Deputy; Edith Smith, Grand Financial Secretary; Fredrick Standford and Martha Tyson, who was master of ceremonies.  Standing : Maleva Hampton, secretary; Jessie Brewer, treasurer; Eva Knox, conductress; Gertrude Platt, assistant conductress; Gertrude Thomas, Rhoda Marx, Irene Austin, Helen Walker, Lillie Brown, Ruth Stoner, Agnes Hill, Geneva Cleveland, Dorothy Wills, Josephine Davis, Pauline Yates, Victoria King and Thelma Hazel. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of members of the Purity Chapter 85, Order of Eastern Star, Seated: Isabel Hunter, James Dukes, Mildred Smith, Esther Green, Eva Crawley, Mary Smith, Edith Smith, Fredrick Standford and Martha Tyson Standing: Maleva Hampton, Jessie Brewer, Eva Knox, Gertrude Platt, Gertrude Thomas, Rhoda Marx, Irene Austin, Helen Walker, Lillie Brown, Ruth Stoner, Agnes Hill, Geneva Cleveland, Dorothy Wills, Josephine Davis, Pauline Yates, Victoria King and Thelma Hazel, gathered around banquet tables celebrating its first anniversary at the Masonic Temple, another version
